<div id="content">
  <div class="search">
    <div class="top"></div>
    <div class="middle">
      <div class="left">
        <h2>Methane gas hydrates sediments around the world</h2>
        <form action="/explore" method="get">
          <h4>Search for your desired location</h4>
          <input type="text" value="Location, Country..." name="name_or_country"/>
          <input type="submit" value="" />
        </form>
        <% features = Feature.order("created_at DESC").limit(7) %>
        <ul>
          <% features.each do |feature| %>
          <li><%= link_to(feature.title, feature_url(feature)) %></li>
          <% end -%>
          <% if !features.empty? %>
          <li><a href="/explore" class="all">view all...</a></li>
          <% end -%>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="right">
        <h2>Explore the world</h2>
        <p>Explore the whole world in<br/>
        the Methane gas hydrates places map</p>
        <a href="/explore" class="explore"></a>
        <p class="random">or <a href="/features/random">go to a random place</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="meaning">
    <div class="top"></div>
    <div class="middle">
      <div class="left">
        <h3>What does methane gas hydrates mean?</h3>
        <p class="hand cufon_handofsean"><span class="quotes open">"</span>Basically is Frozen Heat. Is Ice that can be burned. A very interesting source of energy<span class="quotes close">"</span></p>
        <p>Frozen Heat or Methane Hydrates are a solid clathrate compound (more specifically, a clathrate hydrate) in which a large amount of methane is trapped within a crystal structure of water, forming a solid similar to ice.
          <br/><br/>
          Originally thought to occur only in the outer regions of the Solar System where temperatures are low and water ice is common, significant deposits of methane clathrate have been found under sediments on the ocean floors of Earth.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="/about">Learn more about Frozen heat</a></li>
          <li><a href="/blog">Read more in our blog</a></li>
          <li><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Methane_hydrate" rel="nofollow">Read more at wikipedia</a></li>
          <li><a href="/events">Meet us in an upcoming event</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="right">
        <h5>PHOTOS AND VIDEOS <% if GalleryEntry.count > 0 %><a href="/galleries">View more</a><%end %></h5>
        <% if GalleryEntry.count > 0 %>
          <% entries = GalleryEntry.limit(2) %>
          <% unless entries.empty? %>
            <% entries.each do |entry| %>
              <%= link_to(image_fu(entry.image, :medium), gallery_url(entry.gallery)) %>
            <% end -%>
          <% end -%>
        <% end -%>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="blog_last">
    <div class="top"></div>
    <div class="middle">
      <p class="feed"><a href="<%= blog_rss_feed_url %>">Subscribe to our blog</a></p>
      <% posts = BlogPost.live.limit(3) %>
      <h3>Last in the blog</h3>
      <% unless posts.empty? %>
      <ul>
        <% posts.each do |post| %>
        <li class="<%= cycle('','','last') %>">
          <p class="date"><%= post.published_at.strftime("%d/%m/%Y") %></p>
          <h4><%= link_to post.title, blog_post_url(post) %></h4>
          <p><%= truncate(strip_tags(post.body),
                            :omission => raw("... <a href=\"#{blog_post_url(post)}\">Read more</a>"),
                            :length => 100,
                            :preserve_html_tags => true) %></p>
        </li>
        <% end -%>
      </ul>
      <% end -%>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom"></div>
  </div>
</div>